    <title>Demonstrations</title>
    <shortdesc>A number of short demonstrations are available which describe each part of the NHS
        Data Model and Dictionary, step by step, in an easy to understand screen capture including a
        voice over and readable captions.</shortdesc>
    <body>
        <p><b>Please note that the information contained in the demonstrations was correct at the
                time of publication.</b></p>
        <p>If you are not familiar with the NHS Data Model and Dictionary, it is recommended that
            you proceed through the demonstrations in the following order.</p>
        <p>Please note that some of the demonstrations are followed by three questions to check your
            understanding.</p><p>The subjects covered are:</p><ul id="ul_lzs_x44_n4b">
                <li>
                    <div><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/about/index.html" format="html"
                            scope="external">About the NHS Data Model and Dictionary Page</xref>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div>
                        <xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/help_and_guidance/index.html" format="html"
                            scope="external">Help and guidance Page</xref>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/components/index.html" format="html"
                    scope="external">NHS Data Model and Dictionary Components</xref>
            </li>
                <li>
                <xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/classes/index.html"
                    format="html" scope="external">Classes</xref></li>
                <li>
                    <div><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/attributes/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">Attributes</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div><xref
                        href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/data_elements/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">Data Elements</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/data_sets/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">Data Sets</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div><xref
                        href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/Business_Definitions/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">NHS Business Definitions</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div>
                    <xref
                        href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/supporting_information/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">Supporting Information</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div>
                    <xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/all_items_index/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">All Items Index</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/release_history/index.html"
                    format="html" scope="external">Release History</xref></li>
                <li><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/change_request/index.html"
                    format="html" scope="external">How to Read an NHS Data Model and Dictionary
                    Change Request</xref>.</li>
            </ul><div>At the end of each demonstration, you can choose where you want to go next, you can
            either:</div><ul id="ul_mzs_x44_n4b">
                <li>
                    <div>Navigate through all the demonstrations in the order above (recommended for
                    new users)</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div>Return to <xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/help/help_and_guidance.html" format="html"
                            scope="external">Help and Guidance</xref></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div>Navigate to the <xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/index.html"
                            format="html" scope="external">Front Page of the NHS Data Model and
                            Dictionary</xref>.</div>
                </li>
            </ul><p>Once you have completed the demonstrations, there are two quizzes to check your
                understanding of the demonstrations and the navigation options:</p><ul
                id="ul_nzs_x44_n4b">
                <li>
                    <div>
                        <xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/knowledge_check/index.html"
                            format="html" scope="external">Knowledge Check of the
                            Demonstrations</xref>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div><xref href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/elearning/navigation/index.html"
                        format="html" scope="external">Navigation Exercises</xref>.</div>
                </li>
            </ul><p><b>The content of these demonstrations is for training purposes only and
                    therefore may not match the current content of the NHS Data Model and
                    Dictionary.</b></p><p>Please refer to the <xref
                        href="https://datadictionary.nhs.uk/index.html" format="html"
                        scope="external">NHS Data Model and Dictionary</xref> for the latest version
                    of the NHS Data Model and Dictionary.</p><p><b>How to use the Demonstrations</b></p><ul id="ul_pzs_x44_n4b">
                <li><b>Demonstration start:</b> When the demonstration opens, click on the play
                    button.<p/><image href="../images/demo_start.png" id="image_mdb_tqf_r4b"
                /><p/></li>
                <li>
                    <div><b>Playback Control bar:</b> This appears at the bottom of every page.
                        Titles for the controls will appear when you hover over them.</div>
                </li>
            </ul><image href="../images/control_bar.png" id="image_pgt_vw5_p4b"/>
            <p>The Playback Control bar controls are explained below:</p><ul id="ul_qzs_x44_n4b">
                <li>
                    <div>
                        <image href="../images/rewind.png" id="image_lqn_zw5_p4b"/>
                        <b>Rewind:</b>&nbsp; This control allows you to rewind back to the beginning
                        of the demonstration<p/></div>
                </li>
                <li><image href="../images/play.png" id="image_t2f_bx5_p4b"/>
                    <image href="../images/pause.png" id="image_orf_cx5_p4b"/>
                    <b>Play / Pause: </b>This control allows you to play or pause a
                    demonstration<p/></li>
                <li>
                    <image href="../images/go_back.png" id="image_kwf_dx5_p4b"/><b>Back:</b> This
                    control allows you to 'rewind' a demonstration at specific intervals<p/></li>
                <li><image href="../images/forward.png" id="image_ox1_2x5_p4b"/>
                    <b>Forward:</b> This control allows you to go forward in a demonstration at
                    specific intervals<p/></li>
                <li><image href="../images/fast_forward.png" id="image_kp5_2x5_p4b"/>
                    <b>Fast Forward:</b> This control allows you to fast forward through the
                    demonstration<p/></li>
                <li><image href="../images/audio_on.png" id="image_y3q_fx5_p4b"/>
                    <image href="../images/audio_off.png" id="image_lps_gx5_p4b"/><b>Audio On /
                        Off:</b> This control allows you to turn the audio on or off<p/></li>
                <li><image href="../images/closed_captioning.png" id="image_smq_hx5_p4b"/>
                    <b>Closed Captioning:</b> If you do not have access to a PC with sound then you
                    can view the closed caption by clicking on the CC button.</li>
            </ul>
    </body>
